Privacy Policy for Trackwise App

Effective Date: 27 Aug 2023

This Privacy Policy describes how [Your Company Name] ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and shares personal and non-personal information when you use the Trackwise mobile application (the "App").

Information We Collect

Personal Information:
We do not collect any personally identifiable information ("personal information") from users of the App.

Non-Personal Information:
The App may collect non-personal information such as device information, usage statistics, and interactions within the App. This information is collected to improve the App's functionality and user experience.

Data Storage

The App stores certain data locally on your device, such as preferences, settings, and user-generated content. This data is stored solely for the purpose of providing a seamless user experience and is not transmitted to our servers or third parties.

Third-Party Services

The App may display advertisements provided by third-party advertising networks. These advertisements may use cookies and similar technologies to collect non-personal information about your interactions with the advertisements. Please note that we do not have control over the information collected by third-party advertisers.

Children's Privacy

The App is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will delete the information.

Changes to Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We encourage you to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed about our data practices.

Contact Us

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests related to this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at parthiban.rajalingam@gmail.com.
